"Needs as defined by health professionals. # Types of Medical Problems\nMedical problems can be divided into three main categories. & Universal problems This category includes, for example, non-specific diarrheal diseases, upper and lower respiratory infections, skin infections, scabies, intestinal parasitic infections, joint pain, cardiovascular ailments, etc. These pathologies are all found in both normal and emergency situations, but in emergencies they are much more prevalent and much more serious than they are normally."